default3.3 
defaultIncreasing 
defaultthe 
defaultuse of innovative 
defaultmethods 
defaultto 
defaultdetect
default early stages of
default 
defaultestablishment of INNS. 
default&#xa0;
defaultGovernment and others should make more use of innovative methods to detect the early stage of INNS establishment where these are practicable 
defaultFor example, hair tubes for mammals 
defaultand collections of faeces 
defaultfrom which DNA can be extracted to identify species and also individuals; e (environmental) DNA – which can be used to track presence of non-native invasive amphibians such as bullfrogs in ponds for example; camera
default traps. Much of the data collection can be done by volunteers but would need coordinating with state agencies and analysing by scientists.
default&#xa0;
default3.4 T
defaulthe minimum requirements for successful management 
defaultof INNS
