defaultRealistic and appropriate prioritisation based on risk assessment for native wildlife, people and the economy
default. This could lead to risk-
defaultbased trading of species such as 
defaultINNS of 
defaultaquatic plants
default3.4.2 Consultation with local people leading to r
defaultapid decision making leading to rapid action
default3.4.3 
defaultAction at the appropriate scale (e.g. 
defaultfor 
defaultbankside
default INNS plants such as Japanese knotweed,  whole water 
defaultcatchments rather than
default just one 
defaultpart of the 
defaultcatchment where the species is known and conspicuous
default)
default3.4.4 
defaultCriteria for success agreed early in the project
default, and success/failure reported on at milestones and at the end of the project.
