defaultWill the EU Directive be sufficiently sensitive to th
defaulte need to p
defaultrevent 
defaultthe
default spread of potentially invasive species from EU Member states where 
defaultthey are either 
defaultnative
default or 
defaultlong established to those where not yet established but where they could cause harm.
default&#xa0;
default3.8.2. 
default How do we prioritise (we cannot manage all INNS everywhere)? 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe should focus on s
defaulttrengthen
defaulting
default existing legislation
default. The
default Scottish model looks promising.
default E
defaultcological priorities
default should be based
default on global responsibilities
default, for example the
default removal of rats from seabird islands. Societal and economic benefits from managing INNS may
default however need to
default be based on different priorities
default, for instance 
defaultkeeping new plant diseases out of publicly accessible heritage gardens, and clearing away Himalayan balsam to allow access to river banks by anglers.
